Smoked Chipotle Gouda Mac and Cheese! This Ooey Gooey, Rich, Bold, and Creamy Mac is IT and so delicious!! Give this recipe a try share with someone you know will enjoy. Full recipe below!  👇🏾 
#macandcheese #smokedgouda #creamy #ooeygooey 
Ingredients 

1 lb. Cellentani Pasta 
4 tablespoon unsalted butter 
3 tablespoons AP Flour 
32 oz.Heavy Cream 
8.oz Pepper jack cheese
16 oz Smoked Gouda grated -divided 
16oz Sharp cheddar - save some for topping 
8.oz Mozzarella cheese 
8 oz. Cream cheese 
Dash of hot sauce
2 tablespoon yellow Mustard  
Pinch of Nutmeg 
2 teaspoon chipotle powder 
¼ teaspoon cayenne pepper 
2 teaspoon smoked paprika 
1 ½ teaspoon garlic powder 
1 ½ teaspoon onion powder 
Salt & freshly cracked black pepper to taste 
Note: Season pasta. I used salt, pepper, and garlic powder. 

Instruction: 

1. Preheat the oven to 350°F. 2. Cook pasta to al dente according to package directions. Be sure to rinse pasta with cold water after straining and lightly coat with olive oil.  3. In a large pot, heat butter over medium-low heat. Once butter has melted, add in flour, and whisk until the flour is combined well.  4. Slowly add in heavy cream. Stir and let mixture start to boil lightly.  Add cream cheese, cheeses, and spices, remember to save some cheddar for your topping and half of the smoked Gouda for layering when adding Mac to your cast iron. Whisk until all cheese has melted, and add in your mustard and hot sauce. 5. Add in pasta and mix until fully incorporated. Make sure all pasta is covered in sauce. 6. Transfer your mixture layering with smoked Gouda cheese, into a large cast iron or lightly greased baking dish, then top with sharp cheddar. Bake for 30 minutes or until mac and cheese is golden and bubbly throughout. Feel free to broil on low for 2-3 minutes if you need more color after the 30 minutes. 7. Let cool and enjoy!

Brussel Sprout lovers this one’s for you. These Sweet and Spicy glazed Brussels make the perfect side dish for any meal. I added some fresh orange juice, mint , and cilantro which really brought a really fresh flavor to these Brussels give them a try full recipe below 👇🏾 #brusselsprouts #sweetandspicy #panseared 

Ingredients 
1 pound Brussels sprouts (trimmed and cut in half lengthwise)
2 tablespoon olive oil + more for cooking 
Salt and pepper to taste 
Juice of ½  orange 
½ teaspoon grated ginger
⅓ cup maple syrup 
⅓  teaspoon red pepper flakes (or to your liking )
1 tablespoon fresh cilantro chopped 
1 tablespoon fresh mint chopped 
Garnish sesame seeds (optional)

Instructions 
1. Cut and clean Brussels. Season with salt, pepper, red chili flakes, and olive oil. 2. Heat a large cast iron over medium high for 3-4 minutes. Add more olive oil. As soon as the oil is hot, swirl to coat the pan. Then add the seasoned halved Brussels sprouts. Shake the skillet a little and move them so that as many as possible are cut-side down. Let sit completely for at least 4 minutes, until they develop charred caramelized sear 3. Continue cooking by adding orange juice and maple syrup stirring every few minutes, until the Brussels sprouts are browned and nicely coated, sprouts will have a crisp, caramelized outside and tender but firm inside. 4. Remove the pan from the heat. Add to a mixing bowl and add fresh chopped herbs and sesame seeds and enjoy hot!

Who doesn’t love a good one pot chicken dinner! Blackened Chicken with Tomato Turmeric rice. This recipe uses very simple ingredients to make a very delicious dinner full recipe below! 

Ingredients 
2 lb. chicken thighs (about 6 pieces) 
1 teaspoon Cayenne pepper 
1 teaspoon Garlic powder
½ teaspoon Smoked paprika 
¼ teaspoon Allspice 
1 tablespoon Blackened seasoning blend 
1 1/2 teaspoon Kickn chicken seasoning weber 
Salt pepper to taste 
1 tablespoon olive oil

Rice
1 ½ cups long grain rice washed 
2 garlic cloves minced garlic
1 teaspoon grated ginger 
1 small shallot chopped  
1 cube chicken bouillon 
Salt pepper to taste 
¼ ground cumin
¼ teaspoon turmeric 
Enough chicken stock to cover rice about 2 ½ cups 
½ cup crushed tomatoes 
1 ½ teaspoon adobo 
3 Sprigs of cilantro 

Instructions 
1. Add the cleaned chicken thighs to a bowl with oil and all seasonings mix until the chicken is well coated. 2. In a medium pot, heat up olive oil on medium high heat, Add your chicken thighs skin side down and sear for about 3-4 minutes on each side until golden brown. Remove the chicken and place in a bowl and set aside.  3. In the same pot sauté the shallots, garlic, and ginger until translucent. Stir in the rinsed rice and cook for about a minute or two making sure it doesn’t stick to the bottom of the pan. Pour in the tomato paste and chicken stock over the rice and add all seasonings,and about 3 sprigs of cilantro, mix well.  4. Add chicken thighs over the rice then cover the pot and cook on low-medium heat for about 15 to 20 minutes or you can add your pot to a 350 degree oven and bake for about 30 minutes. When the rice is done it should be fluffy. Enjoy!

Holiday Mulled Wine is perfect for winter and holiday entertaining! It is very easy to make SO cozy, and warming with lots of fragrant flavor you’ll definitely be enjoying at least 3 glasses at your next gathering haha, full recipe below! 
 #mulledwine #cocktails #cozy #redwine #holidays 

Ingredients 
2 (750 ml) bottle of dry red wine
¾ cup brandy 
2 orange, sliced into rounds 
2 apples sliced 
1 pear sliced 
10 whole cloves 
5 cinnamon sticks 
3 star anise 
⅓ cup maple syrup 
⅓ cup honey 
1 teaspoon nutmeg ground or freshly grated 
garnishes: citrus slices (orange) extra cinnamon sticks, extra star anise. 

1. Combine wine, brandy, honey, maple syrup, orange slices, apples, pears, cloves, cinnamon, star anise, to a large pot. Stir to combine. 2. Cook the mulled wine on low/ medium heat until it reaches a very light simmer. You don’t want it to boil. Cover, and let the wine simmer for at least 30 minutes. 3. Strain and taste. You can always add more honey or maple syrup  to make it sweeter. 4. Serve warm in a heat proof mug or glass, topped with garnishes. Enjoy!

Savory Roasted Garlic and Thyme Sweet Potato mash, such a perfect combination with just a hint of sweetness these potatoes make the perfect holiday side dish. Full recipe below! 
#sweetpotatomash #thyme #roastedgarlic 
ingredients 
8-10 large sweet potatoes
1 tablespoon salt for boiling and more to season 
4 cups vegetable broth
small bundle of fresh thyme
4 bay leaves
1 cup salted butter 
1/2 to 3/4 cup heavy cream depending on consistency you’re looking for 
Ground black pepper to taste 
⅛ teaspoon ground nutmeg
1 head of roasted garlic  
salt to taste 

For Roasted Garlic 
1. One or more whole heads of garlic using a sharp knife, cut 1/2 inch from the top of cloves. Season with a pinch of salt, pepper and a drizzle of Extra virgin olive oil, wrap in foil and bake at 400 F for 30-35 minutes until garlic is browned and soft when you press it.  
For mash 
1. Fill a large pot with cold water about half way and add vegetable broth. Peel and cut potatoes into large cubes. Place the potatoes into the pot, then add salt, thyme and bay leaves. Cover the pot and bring the potatoes to a boil. Simmer until the potatoes are fork tender. 2. Drain the potatoes and remove the thyme stems and the bay leaves. Add butter, and 1 head of roasted garlic to potatoes. 3. Next, add in ¼ cup cream and more to your liking, nutmeg and a bit of ground black pepper. Use a potato masher and mash the potatoes for a few minutes, until smooth and creamy. Taste the sweet potatoes and add more cream and salt if necessary. Enjoy!

Chocolate Chip Belgian Waffles! These waffles are perfectly crisp on the outside with the fluffiest center. Share this recipe with someone you know would enjoy! Full recipe below  
#chocolatechipwaffles #belgianwaffle #breakfast #chocolate 

Ingredients 
1 ½ package active dry yeast 
¼ cup sugar
¾ cup lukewarm milk
3 eggs 
3 Cups Flour
2 teaspoon vanilla extract 
1 teaspoon Nutmeg 
1 cup melted butter
Pinch of salt 
½ cup chocolate chips 
Maple Syrup 

1. In a large bowl add lukewarm milk, sugar, active dry yeast, and mix. Let sit for 15 min until yeast turns into soft foam.
2. Add in vanilla extract, eggs, melted butter, nutmeg, and mix together.
3. In a large separate bowl, add flour, a pinch of salt, then create a well in flour. Slowly add liquid mixture into well. 
4. Mix batter with rubber spatula or hand until soft dough. Put a kitchen towel over the bowl and let sit in a warm place for 30 min until dough rises. *Tip Place bowl in oven (as your “warm place”) on lowest setting possible* 
5. After the dough rises, add in chocolate chips. Mix together until evenly distributed. Heat up the waffle maker, add non-stick spray or butter evenly, add about a tennis ball size of dough on high heat, cook for about 4-5 minutes (keep a close eye until dough has turned a honey brown)  FINISH!
6.Enjoy with your choice of syrup!

French fries are cool but let’s make some delicious crispy oven baked hasselback potatoes with a Fresh Basil & Cilantro gremolata. These are a bit more show stopping than your average potato! Full recipe below  👇🏾 
#hasslebackpotatoes #crispy #gremolata 
Ingredients 
For Potatoes 
1lb. Yellow Baby Potatoes 
1 tablespoon Smoked paprika
1 tablespoon Garlic powder
Pinch of Maldon salt 
½ teaspoon Cayenne pepper 
Black pepper to taste
1 tablespoon Dried oregano

Basil & Cilantro gremolata
1 lime juice
2 garlic cloves
1 cup fresh cilantro
1 cup fresh basil
Salt to taste 
Pinch of chili flakes 
¼ cup olive oil 

Instructions 
1. Preheat the oven to 350°F. Wash your potatoes and pat them dry. 2. Use a sharp kitchen knife to cut each potato into slices about 1/4-inch apart. Make sure you don’t cut all the way down to the bottom. I find the best way to do this is to use 2 chop sticks as seen in the video, to prevent you from cutting all the way through.  3. Once all of your potatoes are sliced, place them in a bowl and evenly toss with oil and spices then a baking tray. Make sure the potatoes are all facing cut-side up before baking for at least 40 minutes. The potatoes will be crispy on the outside and soft on the inside when they are done. 4. Serve hot with gremolata and Enjoy!  

For Gremolata
1. Add chopped cilantro, basil, garlic, lime juice, olive oil, chili flakes, and salt in a small bowl and mix well. Taste. Add more lime to your liking or chili flakes for more heat.

Bbq dry rub chicken! Lots of spices rubbed on chicken quarters and smoked, spritzing with orange juice to keep moisture and add flavor! So simple yet extremely delicious. Full recipe below. 
#bbqdryrub #smokedchicken #meatermade 

Ingredients 
2 lb. chicken quarters cleaned 
1 cup Smoked paprika 
1 cup Brown sugar
2 tablespoons Chili powder 
⅓ cup Garlic powder
⅓ cup Onion powder
3 tablespoons Applewood Smoked salt 
2 tablespoon Cayenne pepper
2 tablespoon Salt 
1 tablespoon freshly cracked pepper
1 cup of Orange juice 
½ cup Olive oil   

1. Set Traeger temperature to 325℉ and preheat with the lid closed for 15 minutes.
2. Mix all spices in a bowl.
3. Rub a generous amount of Bbq dry rub on chicken.
4. Insert the probe into the thickest part of a chicken quarter, avoiding the bone. Place the chicken directly on the grill grates, close the lid, and cook until the internal temperature reaches 165°F. Half way through the cooking time spritz with orange juice and smoke for about 50 minutes. 
5. Remove the chicken from the grill and let it rest for 5 minutes before serving. Enjoy!

A super comforting dish, packed with so much flavor Shrimp N’ Grits with @wusthof 

February is Black History Month, but over here we celebrate black history everyday!  This is hands down one of my favorite dishes, and a staple in black cuisine. This is also my go to when dining out for brunch. With the help of 
WÜSTHOF superior quality, sharp premium design, with ease I was able to prepare everything for this popular dish with no worries. Full recipe below 

I’m using the Classic 3”Hollow edge flat pairing knife and Classic 8” Half Bolster Chefs Knife. 
#mywusthof #wusthofpartner #blackhistorymonth 

1 ½ lbs. Shrimp cleaned and deveined
1 tablespoon smoked paprika
½ tablespoon garlic powder
½ tablespoon onion powder
2 teaspoon OldBay seasoning
¼ teaspoon cayenne pepper
1 large red onion chopped
2 bell peppers, diced
2 garlic cloves minced
1 lb. cooked & chopped bacon
3 tablespoon tomato paste
2 tablespoon flour
2 cups chicken stock
Juice from ½ of a lemon
¼ cup Worcestershire sauce
Salt and pepper
seasoning to taste 
 Garnish 2 scallions
For Grits
½ cup Grits
4 cups chicken stock
1 cup parmesan cheddar
½ cup sharp cheddar cheese
4 tablespoon butter
Heavy cream
Salt & pepper to taste
 Instruction 
1. Bring chicken stock to a boil in a medium saucepan over high heat. Whisk in grits, and cook, whisking constantly, for 60 seconds. Cover and reduce heat too low, cook for 30 minutes or until grits are tender and liquid is absorbed. Stir in cheese, butter, cream and serve immediately.
2. Prepare all veggies for sauce and set aside.
3. Add shrimp to a medium bowl and sprinkle with seasoning, mix well.
4. In a large skillet over medium heat cook bacon until browned and crispy.
5. In the same pan once bacon is done sear shrimp for about 2 minutes on each side.
6. Remove shrimp and set aside, next add in red onion, bell peppers, garlic, tomato paste, flour, chicken stock, Worcestershire sauce, a squeeze of lemon and stir until combined.
7. Be sure to taste as you go and add more seasoning to your liking.
8. Add back in bacon, and shrimp to sauce.
9.  To assemble, add grits to your bowl and top with mixture, garnish with scallions and enjoy!

Irish you can taste the love in this pickle brisket sammy! 🥪

P.S. don’t forget the green beer. Sláinte! 🍺

Recipe:
Smoked Pickle Brisket
3 lb brisket
3 qt pickle juice
1 tbsp fresh coarsely ground black pepper 
1 tbsp whole coriander seeds
1 tbsp coriander powder
1/2 tsp whole yellow mustard seeds 
Rye Bread
Swiss cheese

Sando Sauce
1/2 cup mayonnaise
1/4 cup ketchup-style
1 tbsp shallot
2 tsp prepared horseradish
1 tbsp Worcestershire sauce 
1 tsp smoked paprika
1/4 tsp dry mustard
2 tbsp relish

Coleslaw
14 oz coleslaw mix
1/2 cup mayonnaise
2 tbsp sugar
2 tbsp lemon juice
1 tbsp white vinegar
1/4 tsp kosher salt
1/2 tbsp coarse ground black pepper 
1 tsp celery salt

Instructions
1. Place brisket in mason jar, pour the pickle brine over brisket and let brine for 5 days.
2. After brining, remove the brisket from the brine and pat dry with paper towels. Place the
brisket, fat-side up.
3. In a spice grinder, coarsely grind all the spices. Cover the fat side of the brisket with the peppercorn-coriander mixture.
4. When ready to cook, set the Traeger to 225°F.
5. Place the brisket directly on the grill grates, spiced side up. Insert the MEATER probe into the
thickest part of the brisket and set the target temperature to 204°F. 
6. Set custom alert to remove from the grill and tightly wrap in foil at 160°F. Return to the grill and continue cooking.
7. When MEATER tells you it’s time to remove from heat, allow it to rest before slicing. 

Assembling
1. On a piece of rye bread, add sauce followed by slices of swiss cheese, then slices of pickled brisket topped with slaw and another slice of bread cut in half and enjoy!

#MEATER #MEATERmade

Tuna Tartare me please! Made some Ginger Tuna Tartare with Sea salt Plantain chips. This beauty was truly perfection! Full recipe down below 👇🏾 where my Tuna Tartare lovers at 👀 

#tunatartare #plantainchips #avocado #soysauce #ponzu #freshness #cheflife #foodie #seasalt

Ingredients 
2 Green plantain 
1 ½ lbs  Fresh Ahi Tuna 
3 tablespoon Scallion chopped
1 teaspoons sriracha or more for heat   
¼ cup Soy sauce
2 tablespoons Lime Ponzu 
2 teaspoons Sesame oil 
½ cup chopped Cilantro 
2 teaspoons Ginger grated 
1 teaspoons Garlic grated 
Pinch of black and white Sesame seeds 
Garnish with Micro Cilantro 
Oil for frying 
For Avo mash 
2 Avocados 
Lime juice to your liking 
Salt to taste 
1 Minced jalapeños seeds removed 

Instructions 
1. Pat fresh Tuna filet dry using a paper towel.  2. Use a sharp knife to dice the tuna into 1 ½  inch dice. Try to keep all the pieces the same size. 3. Mix all the marinade ingredients in the same bowl, as the tuna and mix well. Refrigerate until ready to assemble. 4. For the avocado, mix everything together in a separate bowl. For plantains 
1. Cut off the ends of each plantain and peel.Cut in half crosswise. 2. Using a mandoline slice plantains lengthwise into preferred thickness for chips. 3. Fill a large skillet halfway with oil. Set over medium-high heat until the oil reaches 350°F. Add plantain fry, until golden brown finish with sea salt. 4. Assemble: Take a mold or ramekin. Start by placing the avocado at the bottom layer and press it down. Now add in the tuna layer and press it down. Garnish with Micro herbs and carefully remove the mold and enjoy with plantain chips!

Garlic Parmesan wings! Super easy to make Crispy wings tossed in garlic buttery goodness, I can eat a ton of these in one sitting! Full recipe below 👇🏾 
#wings #garlicparmesanwings #crispy #delicious #chef #reelsinstagram #contentcreator #tasty #delicious #ranch 

🎥: @jaorik 💫 
 
Ingredients 
1lb.  Wings 
2 teaspoon Garlic powder 
2 teaspoons Onion powder
½ tablespoon Chicken bouillon seasoning 
½ tablespoon Smoked paprika
Salt and pepper to your liking
Vegetable oil for frying  
2 cups AP Flour seasoning listed down below 

For garlic parm sauce 
1 cup Kraft grated Parmesan cheese (divided) ½ in sauce ½ for topping 
⅓ cup Chopped parsley 
1 1/2 tablespoon Minced garlic 
1 teaspoon Dried thyme 
2 teaspoons Chili powder 
1 ½ stick butter 
 
1. Clean chicken wings well and pat dry. 2. Add wings to a bowl and add all seasonings listed, mix well.  3. In a separate bowl add flour and season with salt pepper and 2 tablespoons of garlic powder. 4. Heat a pot up with oil. 5. Dip each wing into the flour mixture then gently place it in the hot oil, do it with the remaining wings then deep fry for 8-10 minutes depending on how big the chicken wings are or until golden brown. Remove from oil and drain. 6. In a saucepan, melt butter then mix all ingredients listed for sauce. Toss in the fried chicken wings in this mixture then place on a serving platter garnished with more parmesan cheese and serve hot! Enjoy.

Waddle you do without these amazing duck and fries? 🤤

Meat
2 duck breasts
2 tbsp @traegergrills Fin & Feather Rub
¼ cup duck fat
1 cup orange juice
¼ cup ponzu
½ cup honey
2 tbsp apricot jam
S&P to taste

Truffle Parmesean Fries
5 lrg russet potatoes
1 cup flour, seasoned
1 tbsp garlic powder
1 tbsp smoked paprika
3 garlic cloves, minced
¼ cup parsley, chopped
2 tbsp @sauce Truff truffle oil
⅓ cup parmesan cheese
Oil for frying

Instructions
1. Preheat @traegergrills to 225°F.
2. Use a sharp knife to crosshatch the duck skin and season both sides of the duck with @Traeger Fin & Feather Rub
3. Insert MEATER probe and set up cook to preferred temperature, we did 140°F. 
4. Place the duck breasts, skin-side up, on the grate and cook until MEATER app tells you to remove from grill and  allow it to rest. 
5. In a hot pan, sear the duck skin until golden brown. In the same pan add orange juice, ponzu, honey, apricot jam, and simmer until thick. 
6. Slice and serve with glaze.

For Truffle fries
1. Cut potatoes to your liking and rinse the potatoes well, washing off as much starch as possible.
2. Combine flour, garlic powder, and paprika. Then, coat potatoes with the flour mix.
3. In a deep fryer with hot oil, add the fries and fry until crispy and golden brown.
4. Once done, in a saucepan melt butter, garlic, and parsley, and pour over fries.
5. Drizzle with @sauce Truff truffle oil and sprinkle with parmesan cheese and enjoy!

Let us guac your world. 🌍😎

Ingredients 
1 tomahawk
Fogo Charcoal rub
3 whole garlic bulb 
2 tbsp mayonnaise
1 tsp S&P

Avocado Chimichurri 
1 cup cilantro leaves, firmly packed
1 ½  cup Italian parsley leaves, firmly packed
¼ cup red wine vinegar 
2 tsp roughly chopped garlic
½ tsp kosher salt
½ tsp ground cumin
½ tsp crushed red pepper
½ cup extra-virgin olive oil
1 whole avocado 
2 jalapeños, seeds removed 
1 tbsp lemon juice
S&P to taste

Tomahawk Steak 
1. Preheat the Traeger to 275°F. 
2. Cut off the top of the garlic bulb season with mayo, salt and pepper. Then, wrap in foil and smoke for at least 1 hour until soft. 
3. Season the tomahawk generously with the FOGO Charcoal rub.
4. Insert the probe into the center of a tomahawk steak, avoiding the bone. And set up cook with the target temperature of 125°F or to your desire. Place the steaks directly on the grill grates, close the lid, and smoke until MEATER tells you to remove from heat.
5. After the tomahawk is rested, heat a cast iron skillet over medium heat and sear all slides! Enjoy with smoked garlic spread and Avo-Chimi Sauce.

Instructions for Avo-Chimi Sauce 
1. In a blender or food processor, add the cilantro, parsley, red wine vinegar, garlic, salt, cumin, and crushed red pepper.
2. Blend well and scrape the sides as needed.
3. With the machine running on low, slowly add the olive oil in a thin steady stream.
4. Continue to blend on medium-high speed until smooth and slightly thickened, for about 60 seconds. Season with S&P to taste.

1. In a bowl, marinate the shrimp in the buttermilk, curry powder, garlic powder, smoked paprika, onion powder, and grated ginger for 15 minutes.
2. In a separate bowl add AP flour and Cornstarch - Feel free 3. to season with garlic powder, salt, pepper, and paprika! 
Heat oil in a wide deep pot, over medium-high heat until the oil reaches 350°F. 
4. Coat Shrimp in AP and Cornstarch mixture. 
Add a handful of the shrimp to the hot oil, fry until the shrimp are golden brown.
5. Set on paper towels and let drain. 
6. Toss Shrimp in bang bang sauce, Fill the warmed tortillas with Shrimp, and slaw mix. Garnish the tacos with cilantro, then serve right away!

Taco ‘bout a fiesta! Get ready to pig out on these pork belly tacos

Ingredients
5lb. Pork Belly, skin removed (leave some fat)
3 tbsp smoked paprika 
2 tbsp garlic powder 
1 tbsp chili powder 
S&P to taste
1 cup crumbled cotija cheese 
Taco tortilla
 
Mango Salsa 
2 cups diced fresh mango 
½ red onion diced 
½ red cabbage, thinly sliced
1 bell peppers, diced 
1 jalapeno, sliced 
1 cup cilantro, chopped 
1 whole lime, juiced
2 tbsp olive oil
Sea salt to taste 
Mix all ingredients in a bowl set aside. 

Avocado Crema 
2 whole avocado 
½ cup sour cream 
1 whole lime, juiced
2 cups cilantro 
3 fresh garlic cloves 
S&P to taste
Water (optional for desired consistency)
Add all ingredients to the blender and blend until smooth. 

Instructions: 
1. Preheat Traeger to 275°F. 
2. In a small bowl, mix together all spices to create a dry rub.
3. Then, score pork belly fat, making 1” cross-hatch throughout.
4. Season generously with dry rub and insert the MEATER probe to the thickest part of pork belly. Then, set up cook to your desired internal temperature, we did 165°F!
5. Place the pork belly fat side up on the grates and smoke until MEATER tells you it’s time to remove from heat and rest.
6. Slice and build your tacos with avocado crema, mango salsa, and cotija cheese! Enjoy.

Rosemary Truffle Potato Chips using @sauce Black Truffle oil! These light crispy delicious chips are perfection and super easy to make! Tag a friend that could use a delicious snack 😎 Full recipe below 👇🏾 
#reels #potatochips #truffleoil #maldonsalt #rosemarychips #snacks #russetpotatoes #asmr 
Ingredients 
4 large Russet potatoes
Maldon salt to taste 
4 cup canola oil for frying 
5 sprigs Rosemary  
2 tablespoons Truff Black Truffle oil 

Instructions
1. Using a mandoline at one of the thinnest settings, slice potatoes. 2. Add all of the potato slices to a large bowl of ice cold water to pull out the starch. Let sit for 30 minutes. 3. After 30 minutes, rinse potato slices and dry well to prepare for frying.  4. Heat oil in a large deep skillet to 350 degrees. 5. Working in batches, add potato slices to hot oil and a few rosemary sprigs stirring until chips are golden browned, remove chips and add to a paper towel lined plate.  6. Once all chips are cooked and cooled add them to a bowl and drizzle truffle oil. Toss to make sure all chips are coated evenly. Sprinkle with more Maldon salt. 7. Enjoy! These won’t last too long, they’re that good.

Did a spin on the Thomas Keller Zucchini! With summer approaching this is the perfect summer side dish Full recipe below 👇🏾 
#thomaskellerzucchini #summervibes #fresh #delicious 
Ingredients 
2 zucchini halved 
1 cup roma tomatoes diced 
½ cup red onion diced
1 serrano pepper diced 
2 limes juiced
Salt to taste  
¾ cup chopped cilantro  
Avocado oil for searing 
1 pound shrimp cleaned & deveined 

Instructions

1. Halve the zucchini lengthwise and score the cut side in a crosshatch pattern. 2. Sprinkle salt on the scored side of the zucchini. Leave the zucchini for 15 minutes. This will draw out moisture from the zucchini.  Pat the zucchini dry with paper towels. 3. Heat oven to 350 F. 4. On medium high heat, place a pan with just enough oil to coat the bottom until oil is hot. Add the zucchini, cut side down, in the oil let the zucchini sear and caramelize without burning. 5. Cook until nice and charred, checking occasionally, Flip zucchini and place in the oven to cook for 5-10 minutes or until the zucchini are completely soft. *I prefer mine not soft so I left it in the oven for about 5 minutes* 6. While it’s in the oven prepare tomato, red onion, serranos, and cilantro, add to a bowl with lime juice to your liking and salt to taste and mix well. 7. For the shrimp, feel free to season with your preferred seasonings and cook on medium heat for 2-3 min on each side.  8. Assemble by placing zucchini on a plate, followed by shrimp and a spoon of tomatoes and enjoy!

Saddle up with this life-changing cowboy butter with prime rib. 🤤

Ingredients
5 lb prime rib roast 
½ cup Fogo Charcoal Rub 
½ cup Traeger Beef Rub 

Cowboy Butter
4 sticks of butter
5 garlic cloves, minced
1 lemon juice 
1 whole lemon, zested
2 tbsp dijon mustard
1 tsp cayenne pepper 
1 tsp paprika
4 tbsp fresh parsley
2 tbsp chives
1 tsp chili flakes
1 tbsp fresh thyme
S&P

Instructions: 
1. Preheat Traeger to 275°F. 
2. Wrap the prime rib with butcher twine and season all around with beef rub and the ends with FOGO Charcoal Rub and set aside.
3. In a bowl, mix together all the ingredients to make the cowboy butter. 
4. Coat the prime rib with half of the cowboy butter and save the other half for later.
5. Insert the MEATER probe into the center of the roast and set up target internal temperature on the MEATER app to your desire (we did 125°F). Place the roast directly on the grill grates, close the lid, and cook until MEATER says it’s time to remove from heat. After resting, serve with melted cowboy butter. A Summer time favorite Elote! Also known as Mexican Street Corn charred on the grill then coated in a delicious creamy sauce topped with cotija cheese, lime zest, cilantro, Tajin, and paprika, a delicious combination of flavors! Full recipe below 👇🏾

Ingredients 
4 ears shucked corn 
½  cup finely crumbled Cotija or feta cheese, plus more for serving
½ cup mayonnaise
½ cup sourcream or Mexican crema
½  teaspoon smoked paprika, plus more for serving
2 limes 1 cut into wedges other for zesting and 1/2 for juicing 
¼ cup finely chopped cilantro leaves 

Instructions
1. Set the grill to high heat and allow it to preheat for 10 minutes.
2. While the grill is heating, combine mayonnaise, sour cream or crema, smoked paprika, lime juice, and salt to taste. Stir well and set aside.
3. When the grill is hot, place corn directly over the hot side of the grill and cook, rotating occasionally, until cooked through and charred in spots on all sides, about 10 minutes.
4. Transfer corn to a plate and use a brush or large spoon to evenly coat corn on all sides with sour cream mixture. Sprinkle it with Cotija cheese, Tajin/paprika powder, chopped cilantro and serve with lime wedges! Enjoy.

Brown Butter Sage Pan seared Scallops simply delicious. recipe down below 👇🏾 

Ingredients 
 10 Fresh Scallops 
1 teaspoon Allspice
¼ teaspoon garlic powder   
1 teaspoon salt 
1 teaspoon fresh cracked black pepper
½ teaspoon dried Oregano 
3 tablespoon salted butter 
5 sage leaves

1. Remove the side muscle from the scallops and rinse. (some scallops are sold with the muscle already removed). Dry the scallops well with a paper towel.  2. In a small bowl combine Allspice, garlic powder, salt, pepper, and dried oregano and use spice blend to season both sides of Scallops. 3. Heat a large cast iron pan over medium-high heat until very hot. Add 1 tablespoon of butter, and swirl to coat the pan. Place the scallops in the pan and sear on the first side without touching or flipping, for about 3 minutes. Using tongs, turn the scallops over, and sear for another 2 minutes, until the scallops are just cooked through. 4. Add in remaining butter and sage and baste scallops. Enjoy!

Watermelon 🍉 Shrimp Ceviche! The perfect sweet/ citrusy refreshing summer time bite full Recipe below👇🏾 

Ingredients 
 1 pound Jumbo Shrimp peeled & deveined cut into 1/2” pieces
½ of a small watermelon small diced 
1 ½ c Fresh Lime juice 
1 c Coconut water
¼ c Olive oil
½ tbsp. Tajin 
 ½ tsp cumin 
1 c Cucumber seeds removed small diced 
½ Red onion fine diced 
2 tbsp Serrano peppers fine diced 
⅓  c chopped mint 
⅓  c Chopped cilantro 
½ tsp Ginger 
Salt & pepper to taste 
Pomegranate - optional 

1. In a bowl combine shrimp and 1 cup of lime juice. Cover and refrigerate until the shrimp are pink. The acid from the lime juice will “cook” the raw shrimp. Drain. Discard the juice.
2. In a separate bowl mix ½ c lime juice, coconut water, olive oil, tajin, cumin, ginger, salt and pepper mix all ingredients and set aside.
3.Add watermelon, serranos, cilantro, mint, shrimp, red onion, cucumber, and ceviche dressing to a bowl gently combine all ingredients.Sit in fridge for 30 minutes.
4. Serve with Tortilla chips Enjoy! 😊

Kombucha Air-Fried Crispy Wings! I used @synergykombucha to make this sauce that had the perfect amount of tang and acidity from the Kombucha, sweetness from the fruit preserves and a whole lot of umami flavor from the Miso. I would even pair this sauce with roasted veggies or salad! Full recipe 👇🏾 

Ingredients 
1 cup Synergy Guava Goddess Kombucha  
1 tablespoon Miso paste 
2 tablespoons Raspberry jam/ preserves
Sesame oil ½ teaspoon
Salt and pepper to taste 

1 Pack party wings 
1 tablespoon Garlic powder 
½ tablespoon Onion powder
1 teaspoon Chicken bullion 
½ tablespoon Paprika
½ teaspoon salt and pepper 
1 cup Cornstarch for coating wings 
coconut oil spray 

Instructions 

1. Place miso paste, fruit preserves, sesame oil, and 1 cup of the kombucha in a bowl and whisk until smooth, add salt and pepper to taste.  2. Preheat air fryer to 375℉ for 5 minutes. 3. Place chicken wings in a medium bowl and season with garlic powder, onion powder, chicken bullion, paprika, salt, pepper, and drizzle olive oil over chicken. Mix well and set aside. 4. Combine corn starch with the garlic powder,salt, pepper and paprika. Sprinkle over wings and toss until thoroughly coated. 5. Dust off any excess cornstarch before placing wings in the air fryer. 6. Spray with oil and cook for 25 minutes, turning once with tongs half way through. Toss with Kombucha sauce and enjoy! Feel free to garnish with scallions and crispy shallots!

Cheddar Buttermilk Biscuits anyone? Buttery flakey deliciousness with just a few simple ingredients - easy for anyone to make! Full recipe below 👇🏾 

Ingredients 
2½ teaspoons baking powder
2 ½ teaspoons sugar
3 teaspoons kosher salt
¼ teaspoon baking soda
3½ cups all-purpose flour
1 cup (2 sticks) chilled! unsalted butter, cut into cubes,more for melted and brushing
1 cup chilled buttermilk 1 cup shredded cheddar cheese 
Flaky maldon salt (optional)

Instructions 

1. Preheat the oven to 400°. Add baking powder, sugar, salt, baking soda, and 3 1⁄2 cups of flour to a bowl. Add those ingredients to a food processor.  2. Add chilled butter and pulse until the  butter looks finely incorporated.  3.Transfer to a large bowl and pour buttermilk over top, tossing with a fork as you go to incorporate.  4. Add in cheddar cheese and mix in a bowl until a shaggy dough forms ( the dough will look a little dry), then turn out onto a clean surface and pat into a 1”-thick square. 5. Using a knife, cut dough into 4 pieces. Stack pieces on top of one another, and press down to flatten with a rolling pin. Roll dough into a 2”-thick rectangle and trim around sides of dough to create clean edges. Cut into a 3x3 grid to make 9 biscuits. 6.  Transfer to a parchment-lined baking sheet, make sure there is enough space apart so biscuits aren’t touching ; freeze 10-15 minutes to make sure butter is as cold as possible before baking. 7. Brush tops of biscuits with melted butter and place in the oven.  8. Bake biscuits until golden brown on top for 15-20 minutes. 9. Sprinkle with Maldon and enjoy!

A cake you need to add to your list of fall treats to bake! My Maple mini Bundt cake with Brown butter glaze. Made with maple syrup in the batter and glazed with a nutty brown butter glaze, topped with honey roasted pistachios, this is the perfect fall treat recipe! Full recipe down below.  

#minibundtcakes #maple #fallbaking #wonderfulpistachios 

Ingredients: Makes 2 dozen mini bundt cakes 

For Maple Cake: 
1 cup Unsalted Butter 1 cup White Sugar 1 cup light brown sugar ⅔ cup Maple Syrup  2 Eggs 1 1/2 tsp. Vanilla Extract 3 cups All-purpose Flour 
 1 cup whole Milk  2 tsp Baking Powder ½  tsp Baking Soda ½ tsp Salt 1 tsp ground cinnamon 1 tsp ground nutmeg 1 cup crushed wonderful Honey roasted Pistachios  
1. Preheat the oven to 350 F. 2. Beat butter and sugars until light and fluffy  3. Add eggs, maple syrup, vanilla extract and incorporate 4. Sift flour, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg ,baking powder and baking soda into the batter, stir in completely 5. Add milk, making sure to incorporate completely 6. Pour into a well greased mini bundt pan and bake for 30-40 minutes, or until a skewer inserted comes out clean 7. Remove the bundt cake from the oven and let it sit for 10 minutes, then flip it upside down onto a cooling rack and remove from the pan. Let cool completely before decorating with brown butter glaze and pistachios.  
Brown butter glaze:
3 cups powdered sugar 1 cup (2 stick) salted butter 6  tablespoons milk of choice  2 teaspoon almond extract 
Instructions 
In a small saucepan over medium heat, melt the butter. Allow the butter to melt, to brown it should take about 6-7 minutes. The butter should turn golden brown and have brown bits on the bottom. Once browned, turn off heat, add in powdered sugar, and stir to combine. Pour in the milk along with the almond extract and continue mixing until everything is well incorporated.

Entering the pumpkin spice chat with my Cinnamon butter Pumpkin Spice creme brûlée French toast, with a crackling caramelized brown sugar topping, these brioche slices dipped in a pumpkin spice custard are perfect. Full recipe down below! 
#pumpkinspice #cremebrulee #frenchtoast 
For French Toast 
3 eggs
⅔ cup whole milk
½ cup pumpkin puree
3 teaspoons pumpkin spice
3 teaspoons sugar
1 teaspoon vanilla extract 
12 slices thick cut bread brioche
2 tablespoons butter 
Sugar to coat top of bread

Cinnamon Butter
8 tablespoon unsalted butter 
2 tablespoon cinnamon
4 tablespoons brown sugar 

1. Add egg, milk, pumpkin puree, pumpkin spice, vanilla extract, and sugar to a bowl, mix  thoroughly.
2. For cinnamon butter mix all ingredients in a bowl.
3. Put a slice of bread on a plate and spread with cinnamon butter. Next add the top slice of bread. 
4. Dip both sides of bread in the pumpkin custard and let it soak for about 5 seconds on each side. Let the excess drip off, then place it in the skillet to fry until golden and crispy on each side, about 3 minutes per side.
5. Repeat with the rest of the bread, adding more butter to the skillet as needed.
6. Sprinkle each french toast with 1 ½ tablespoon granulated sugar and torch just until caramelized, let cool and serve with whipped cream or preferred toppings.Enjoy!

Whether you call it stuffing or dressing, with the perfect amount of spice and flavor, this Skillet Jerk Cornbread is definitely the twist on the classic that needs to be on your Thanksgiving menu this year!

Ingredients
2 tablespoons olive oil
1 lb ground turkey sausage
1½ Tbsp Walkerswood jerk seasoning
2 carrots, diced
3 celery stalks, diced
1 red bell pepper, seeded and diced
½ medium yellow onion, diced
3 garlic cloves, minced
1 tsp chopped fresh ginger
1 tsp smoked paprika
1 tsp garlic powder
¼ tsp ground nutmeg
¼ teaspoon ground allspice
Salt, to taste
Black pepper, to taste
⅓ cup chopped fresh herbs, such as parsley, rosemary, thyme, and sage, plus more for garnish
2 15.5-oz store-bought cornbreads
1½ cups chicken stock
3 tablespoons unsalted butter, melted

Preparation
1. Preheat the oven to 375°F (190°C).
2. Heat the olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add the turkey sausage and break up with a wooden spoon. Stir in the jerk seasoning and cook for about 6 minutes, until browned and crumbly.
3. Reduce the heat to medium and add the carrots, celery, bell peppers, onions, garlic, ginger, paprika, garlic powder, nutmeg, allspice, salt, black pepper, and herbs. Cook until the vegetables have softened, 5-6 minutes.
4. Crumble the cornbread into the sausage and vegetable mixture, then pour in the chicken stock and mix gently, being careful not to break up the cornbread too much.
5. Garnish with herbs, then evenly pour the melted butter on top.This dressing should be nice and moist, but not soggy.
6. Bake until crisp and golden brown,about 30 minutes.
7. Enjoy!

This decadent Apple crumb cake is packed with warm cinnamon apples and a delightful crumb topping. The cake is moist, with warming spices,and a drizzle of sweet icing! Full recipe down below ⬇️ 
#applecrumb #applecrumbcake #honeymaidgrahamcrackers 
Ingredients 
2 Granny smith apples 
⅔ cup granulated sugar 
2 teaspoons cinnamon powder 
½ cup softened butter 
2 eggs 
2 teaspoon vanilla extract
1 ½ cups flour 
1 ¾ teaspoons baking powder 
1 ½ teaspoon salt 
½ cup whole milk

For Icing
1 cup powder sugar 
2 ½ tablespoons milk 

For crumble 
12 whole cinnamon graham crackers, crushed 
¼ cup brown sugar 
½ cup melted butter 
 
Instructions: 
1.Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F. 
2.Line a 9x5” loaf pan with parchment paper.
3.Peel and cut apples into cubes.
4.Next add to a bowl with granulated sugar and cinnamon, set aside.
5.Using a food processor add graham crackers and pulse. Next add in brown sugar, melted butter, and mix thoroughly with a spoon. 
6.With a hand mixer, beat ½ cup softened butter and ⅔ cup granulated sugar together until fluffy. Add eggs and vanilla extract and mix well.
7.Mix flour, baking powder and salt in a separate bowl, then slowly add to creamed fluffy butter mixture until combined. Next add ½ cup milk into this mix until nice and smooth.
8.Pour half the batter into the pan, and add apple mixture on top of the batter in the pan.
9. Add the remaining batter overtop and top with graham cracker crumble mixture.
10.Bake until a cake tester or toothpick inserted into the middle of the cake comes out clean, about 45 minutes to an hour. 
11.For the icing add powdered sugar with milk and mix until fully combined. Allow the cake to cool before icing and enjoy!

Made some super flavorful Cajun Smothered Turkey wings using Better Than Gravy’s Roasted Turkey Gravy. This premium gravy is ready to use straight out of the jar. Just heat it, eat it, serve it and love it! Find the full recipe below for this cozy delicious meal. #sponsored #BetterThanGravy

Ingredients 
6 turkey wings 
1 tablespoon olive oil for searing
1 ½ tablespoons Cajun seasoning
2 teaspoons Salt 
2 teaspoons black pepper 
1 tablespoon garlic powder
2 teaspoons smoked paprika 
2 teaspoons Worcestershire sauce
½ onion, finely chopped
2 garlic cloves, minced 
2 celery stalk, finely chopped
1 bell pepper, finely chopped
2 small carrot, finely diced 
1 tablespoon Better Than Bouillon Base Chicken plus water
3 sprigs thyme
2 sprigs Rosemary
12 oz. Better Than Gravy Roasted Turkey gravy 

Instructions
1.Season the turkey wings with Cajun seasoning, black pepper, salt, smoked paprika, garlic powder ,and Worcestershire sauce.
2.In a large pan over high heat, add oil and brown turkey wings on both sides. Remove from the pot and set aside on a plate.
3.Add onion, celery, bell pepper, minced garlic, and carrot to the pan and cook until the vegetables have softened.
4.Add turkey wings back to the pan then add Better Than Bouillon Base Chicken with  thyme and rosemary and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to a simmer and cover the pan.
5.Cook for about 2 hours or until the turkey is tender. Enjoy with your favorite sides!

 4 tablespoon Cajun seasoning (2 tablespoons reserved for sauce)

Smoked Chipotle Gouda Mac and Cheese! This  Rich, Bold, and Creamy Mac definitely needs to be on the table for Thanksgiving! Full recipe below!  👇🏾 
#macandcheese #thanksgiving #creamy #holidayrecipes 

Ingredients 
1 lb. Cellentani Pasta 
4 tablespoon unsalted butter 
3 tablespoons AP Flour 
32 oz.Heavy Cream 
8.oz Pepper jack cheese
16 oz Smoked Gouda grated -divided 
16oz Sharp cheddar - save some for topping 
8.oz Mozzarella cheese 
8 oz. Cream cheese 
Dash of hot sauce
2 tablespoon yellow Mustard  
Pinch of Nutmeg 
2 teaspoon chipotle powder 
¼ teaspoon cayenne pepper 
2 teaspoon smoked paprika 
1 ½ teaspoon garlic powder 
1 ½ teaspoon onion powder 
Salt & freshly cracked black pepper to taste 
Note: Season pasta. I used salt, pepper, and garlic powder. 

Instruction: 

1. Preheat the oven to 350°F. 2. Cook pasta to al dente according to package directions. Be sure to rinse pasta with cold water after straining and lightly coat with olive oil.  3. In a large pot, heat butter over medium-low heat. Once butter has melted, add in flour, and whisk until the flour is combined well.  4. Slowly add in heavy cream. Stir and let mixture start to boil lightly.  Add cream cheese, cheeses, and spices, remember to save some cheddar for your topping and half of the smoked Gouda for layering when adding Mac to your cast iron. Whisk until all cheese has melted, and add in your mustard and hot sauce. 5. Add in pasta and mix until fully incorporated. Make sure all pasta is covered in sauce. 6. Transfer your mixture layering with smoked Gouda cheese, into a large cast iron or lightly greased baking dish, then top with sharp cheddar. Bake for 30 minutes or until mac and cheese is golden and bubbly throughout. Feel free to broil on low for 2-3 minutes if you need more color after the 30 minutes. 7. Let cool and enjoy!

Elevating your holiday vibes with these Juicy Pomegranate BBQ chicken thighs. Savoring the festive flavors one sweet and tangy chicken thigh at a time! Full recipe below! 

#holidayrecipes #pomegranate #chickenthighs 

ingredients:
4 skinless boneless chicken thighs 
6 tablespoons olive oil, divided 
¼ teaspoon ground Cumin 
1 teaspoon Garlic powder 
1 teaspoon cayenne pepper 
1 ½ teaspoon Smoked paprika 
Salt & Pepper
1 whole pomegranate cut 
2 tablespoons Parsley  chopped 

For Pomegranate BBQ sauce 
1 cup Ketchup 
⅓  cup molasses
½ teaspoon ground mustard 
3 Tablespoon apple cider vinegar 
½ cup pomegranate juice
⅓ cup maple syrup 
2 Tablespoons Worcestershire sauce
Salt and pepper to taste 

Instructions
1.Add all ingredients to a sauce pan and whisk until fully incorporated. Cook the sauce over medium heat until it starts to bubble. Reduce the heat to medium low and allow it to simmer until it thickens, 20 minutes. Stirring constantly so the BBQ sauce doesn’t burn.
2.When the sauce is thick it should be able to coat the back of the spoon. Remove it from the heat. Set aside.
3. Heat olive oil in a grill pan or large skillet over medium heat.
4. Wash and clean chicken. Pat chicken thighs dry with a paper towel. Season chicken thighs with cumin, garlic powder, smoked paprika, cayenne, salt, and pepper.
5.Add seasoned chicken thighs to the skillet, smooth side down; cook for 8 minutes without moving, and then flip. The chicken should have nice char! Cook until the juices run clear, an additional 10 minutes, depending on the thickness of the chicken thighs.
6. Pour pomegranate bbq sauce over chicken thighs and simmer for 5 minutes.
7. Add to a plate and spoon the sauce over chicken. 
8. Garnish with fresh chopped parsley, and Pomegranate seeds and serve immediately.Enjoy!

Made an Incredible Homemade BBQ Chicken pizza using the new @cuisinart Indoor pizza oven. A delicious restaurant quality pizza with a nice crispy crust in just 5 minutes! See full recipe below 🍕 👇🏾 #Ad #cuisinart_partner

Ingredients 
1 lb. store-bought pizza dough
4 slices bacon chopped 
1 Tablespoon olive oil for searing chicken 
½  small red onion, thinly sliced
1 delicata squash sliced
½ cup your favorite BBQ sauce
2 chicken breast diced 
1 tablespoon rosemary 
1 tablespoon smoked paprika 
Salt & pepper 
1 cup shredded mozzarella cheese
3 slices fresh mozzarella or more for cheesier pizza  
1 bunch chives chopped for garnish

Instructions   

1. If pizza dough is frozen, thaw out.  2. Preheat cuisinart pizza oven to 700°F. Light will go green when ready. 3. Season the cleaned diced chicken breast with rosemary, salt, pepper, smoked paprika, and sear in a hot pan until cooked. This takes about 5-6 minutes. Then remove chicken from the pan. 4. In the same pan add bacon and cook for 4-5 minutes on each side. 5. Next slice red onion and delicata squash, set aside.  6. On a lightly floured work surface using lightly floured hands or rolling pin, gently flatten the dough into a disc. Stretch and flatten the disc into a 12-inch circle, about 1/2-inch thick. Once shaped into a 12-inch circle, create a lip around the edges. Pinching the edges up to create the rim.  7. Top the dough evenly with BBQ sauce. Add the shredded mozzarella cheese, delicata squash, bacon, red onion, and fresh mozz slices and bake for 5 minutes.  8. Garnish with chives, slice hot pizza and serve immediately. Enjoy!

Oh my! THE Best Honey Sriracha Salmon Burger where golden nectar meets fiery spice. A symphony for your taste buds,with a vibrant slaw! secret green sauce? The magic touch! A simple Avocado, Jalapeño aioli. Ingredients listed below. Enjoy! 

#salmonburger #honeysriracha #flavor #cabbageslaw 

Makes 5 burgers 
Ingredients 
2 lb. skinless fresh Salmon
King’s Hawaiian Buns 
½ red onion
⅓ cup Dill
⅓ cup parsley 
3 garlic cloves minced 
1 Lemon zested 
½ cup Bread crumbs 
1 egg 
1 teaspoon Smoked paprika
1 teaspoon Garlic powder 
½ teaspoon ground ginger 
Pinch of salt and pepper 

For the Glaze 
3 tablespoon soy sauce 
¼ cup Honey
½ cup sriracha 

For the Slaw 
½ Red Cabbage thinly  
1 cup Carrots thinly sliced
2 tablespoon Mint chopped
3 tablespoon Cilantro chopped  
1 tablespoon fresh Lime juice 
Drizzle of Olive oil 
Salt and pepper

No bland bowls in 2024! Elevate your bowl game with this healthy Chimichurri shrimp bowl. I enjoyed mine with yellow rice.Fresh, easy, and bursting with flavors—especially with that delightful pineapple 🍍 salsa! 🌱 Recipe down below for shrimp, salsa, and Chimi! 

 #HealthyEating #FlavorfulFeasts #Shrimpbowl 

Ingredients 

1 pound shrimp (peeled and deveined)
2 tablespoons olive oil
1 teaspoon smoked paprika seasoning
¼ teaspoon onion powder
¼ teaspoon garlic powder
 Salt and black pepper
¼ teaspoon allspice

chimichurri 
⅓ cup fresh parsley, roughly chopped
1 fresno chili, finely chopped 
2 garlic cloves, minced 
2 tablespoon shallots, minced
1 tablespoon dried oregano
¼ cup red wine vinegar
⅓ cup olive oil 
Salt and pepper to taste

Pineapple salsa 
½ cup cherry tomatoes, halved 
½ cup black beans 
1 cup pineapple, diced 
1 small jalapeño seeds removed, finely diced  
2 tablespoon lime juice 
¼ cup Cilantro, chopped  
salt to taste 

Instructions 

1. For chimichurri add chopped parsley, shallots, garlic, dried oregano, fresno peppers, vinegar, and oil to a medium bowl mix well season with salt, pepper and set aside. 2. Add pineapple, black beans, tomatoes, cilantro, jalapeño, salt, pepper and lime juice in a bowl combine and set aside.  3. In a bowl, combine raw shrimp, olive oil and seasonings. 4. In a cast iron pan, heat oil on medium/high heat. 5. Note: Putting the shrimp on skewers is optional. Add shrimp to the hot pan and cook for 2 minutes. Flip and cook for another 2 minutes.( A nice char is the key here) 6. Serve in a bowl over yellow rice with pineapple salsa and drizzle with fresh chimichurri! Top it off with avocado if you desire and Enjoy!
